<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>16-1033</num>
  <heading>Civil liability.</heading>
  <text>A law enforcement officer shall not be civilly liable solely because he or she makes an arrest in good faith and without malice pursuant to this subchapter.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 8-261" type="History">Apr. 30, 1991, D.C. Law 8-261, § 2(c)(2), 37 DCR 5001</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 16-1033.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
